<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jyssa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, long time lurker here finally with a question I don't see answered..<P>Have this wonderful spell atone which I use when travelling..haven't had it for long..how do you know if it worked?  I think I am always getting a message that the mob calms down but sometimes when root wears off they aggro on me anyways..<P>also want to thank all of you I have lurked here for grrr long time now, never would have gotten my cleric to 20 let alone 39 without the good advice I've read here...<P>Jyssa</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm.  Haven't cast it for a while and I forget if it gives a message.  It definitely doesn't tell you if it worked or failed.<P>What everyone does is watch the mob.  When it clears aggro, the mob changes direction to path back to where it came from.  Nine times out of ten this will be in a different direction than it is facing now.  Sometimes they even change stance.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zygote</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">some mobs you can also con. when a mob is aggro'd hes always scowl to attack, if you aggro'd a mob that was just threatening or below then he'll go back to his original con.<P>atone does give a message about calming down, there are no resist messages, its also a good idea to get out of aggro range quick.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wamsutta</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The higher a mob's level is, the greater chance you have of needing to atone multiple times to completely wipe yourself off the list.  The message "calms down" is seen every time you hit a target with the spell.<P>Wamsutta<BR>57 Templar, Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Samsara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you know how to circle-strafe, and you have enough room to do it, you can move around in an arc some distance off from the mob.  If he turns to face you as you move, he is still aggroed.  If he doesn't, it's a good sign that atone worked.<P>Make sure you're outside of the mob's normal aggro range when checking in this way, though.<P><P>------------------<BR>Samsara<BR>Holy Cleric of Tunare<BR>The Folk of Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Obek</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I used to do the circle strafe thing until recently.<P>Just atone the mob and /assist the mob.  If it says 'You cannot assist yourself!' then you are still targeted and aggroed.  If you /assist and the mob has no target, then the aggro is clear.<P>When a mob is mezzed the mob will keep the same target until mez is broken, so there is no way to be completely sure.<P>Obek Lifestryder<BR>Templar of < Knights of Force ><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Right.  Forgot about that.  And every good cleric should have a /assist button.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've had mob's that were hitting me turn and walk away when atoned... I don't think range matter's so much as long as it takes.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Range doesn't matter but it's futile to Atone if the mob will immediately aggro on you again.<P>Atoning for travel: Root mob, move out of aggro range, then atone. You can try either assisting the mob or circle strafing to determine if the mob is still aggro. If it is, either run for it or root/atone again.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kitsinu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great trick Obek.  I still learn things I didn't know on this board.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tarf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mobs will not be atoned if they are in midswing or mid cast.  <P>I have had mobs running towards me and got atoned and turned on their heel and walked off.<P>Tarf</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirri, every cleric should have 2 assists buttons  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><BR>1 for regular /assist and a second for /assist a_primary_tank_01</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Connovar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I experimented with atone the other day whilst in seb.  Normally if in the wilderness if a mob aggros I fear it due having quite often to repeatedly cast atone to clear aggro.  Sometimes it works immediately sometimes it doesn't work.  However, in Seb I was atoning mezzed mobs after the enchanter had mezzed, slowed, crippled the mob etc.. and I think the mob only went for the enchanter a couple of times in several hours when I atoned. Seemed to save some mana</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fengother</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've had to use atone twice on some mobs to get them calmed down. I guess they were *really* mad.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I broke out atone the other day in Frontier Mountains hunting rares with a few other 50+ friends.  All the mobs (other then the giant rares) were green.  So I would root (lvl 9 spell) and atone and 9 out of 10 times they would either spin or change how they stood.<P>Great idea on the /assist! Will have to try that next time we go romp.<P>On a day to day basis I dont have room to mem it.  Either I am grouped with an enc who blurs or a shaman who slows.  May try this out though while travelling.  Great tip! Thanks,<P>------------------<BR><B>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara</B><BR>Vicar of Tunare<BR><B>~Calizana Rhinelander</B><BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR><A HREF="http://www.lostorder.com" TARGET=_blank>Lost Order of Akalabeth</A><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sometimes you just won't be able to atone a mob.<P>We were getting ready to do a Ixiblat slaying a little while back.<P>Due to hunting in POG, I'm KOS to that ranger /druid quest guy in BW.  He agroed on somebody in the guild and started running around beating on people in the camp.  We lead him away and I rooted him with Paralyzing earth.<P>I then proceeded to atone him about 8 or 9 times until PE broke and then he came charging for me and started beating me up.<P>We decided it was best to just kill him at that point in time.  So Atone doesn't always work.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>60th Dwarven High Priest<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm, I'm an inky cleric and have hunted in PoG and that ranger/druid guy in BW regarded me as an ally. Could my faction have wrapped? That would be hysterical to hang out in Gfay unmolested, at least by the guards.<P>------------------<BR>Teir' Dal Vicar<BR>Tallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tfodthog</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have used atone in mid combat when a Mob takes a liking to a caster and wont taunt off.  Immediately after that heal to the caster the atone to the mob and he turns to the tank.  It has saved a number of enchanters and wizzies.  I have a hot key for it so they know not to cast until the tank has rebuilt some agro.<BR>  The only worry about this is if you have pets in the group they will need to be retargeted.  It will however pull a Mob pet back to the tank nicely due to the small aoe it has.  I have not had it that long but I really like this spell.<P>Now if I had a reduced MOK at 34th level or so to overwrite those annoying DSs that chew up my tanks I would be really happy. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">GFay faction != PoG faction.  There are about six factions in GFay and only two are hurt by PoG hunting.  The other people in GFay will still eat you alive.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
